'''Alins''' is a [[municipality]] in the [[Comarques of Catalonia|''comarca'']] of the [[Pallars Sobir<U+00E0>]] in [[Catalonia]], [[Spain]]. It covers the valles of the [[Noguera de Vallferrara]] and [[Tor]] rivers in the north of the ''comarca''. The [[Pica d'Estats]] (3142&nbsp;m, the highest point in Catalonia) is on the frontier between the municipality and [[France]]. A local road links the municipality with the L-504 road.

== Subdidvisions ==
The municipality of Alins is formed of seven villages. Those marked with an asterisk are "delocalised municipal entities" 
(''entitats municipals descentralitzades'') and have their own local councils with limited powers.{{ref|EMD}} [[Population]]s 
are given as of 2005:
*'''Ainet de Besan''' (35)*
*'''Alins''' (58)
*'''Ara<U+00F3>s''' (29)*
*'''<U+00C0>reu''' (84)*
*'''Besan''' (5)
*'''Nor<U+00ED>s''' (12)
*'''Tor''' (25), linked with [[Andorra]] by a forest track

